      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">H F ¶ Córdova ¶  8 January 1885 ¶ Baron Ferdinand von Mueller ¶ Melbourne ¶ Respected Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">85.01.08a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Hugo Finck</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M142, Library, Royal Botanical Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Found with specimens of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Quercus</seg> sp. (MEL 2419309).</p>
               </note>Córdova den 8tn Januar 1885<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marked by M: ‘Beantw. 21/4/85 F.v.M.’ [Answered 21 April 1885]. Letter not found.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Herrn Baron Ferdd von Müller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Geehrter Herr</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mein Schreiben vom 6tn Dez. 1884, in welchem ich Ihnen die Versendung einer Blechbüchse mit Eicheln, die ich via London per Mssrs Watson &amp; Scull, Thames Street an Sie absandte, werden Sie erhalten haben.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Per Steamer Esk sandte ich unter ähnlichen Adressen eine zweite Sendung Eicheln in einen Korb verpackt. Der Dampfer verliest Vera Curz für Southhampton den 2tn Januar.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Beifolgend Blatt von Fraxinus? trilobata und einen Zweig von Quercus No 3 (Cozahual), auch ein Blatt einer frisch gekeimten Eichel von No 3.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 6. Quercus sp ? a deciduous oak, 60 to 80 feet high, with excellent timber for all purposes. Its bark is used in tanning. Height above sea 7 to 9.000 feet.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 7. <name key="Quercus%20argentea">Quercus argentea</name>. Deciduous. 80 to 100 feet high; was formerly very abundant, but now nearly extinquished. Good timber for building purposes &amp; durable. Is very ornamental. From 7 to 9.000 ft.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 8. Quercus sp ? deciduous, resembles No 7 in the colour of the leaves, but is quite distinct; 60 to 80 ft high. Its timber is used by wheelwrights &amp; for building purposes. Is a very fine oak. 7 to 9.000 ft.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 9. Unknown oak, of which only a few acorns were delivered to me, without any leaves. 7 to 9.000 ft.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 0. Large leaved <name key="Quercus%20virens">Quercus virens</name>, live oak; 3.000 ft above sea. Could obtain only a few acorns, as most live oaks gave no fruit during last year.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In dieser Woche sende ich einen Mann in die Gebirge um Tannen und Fichtenzapfen zu sammeln.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Alle die verschiedenen Aufträge, welche ich gegeben habe, waren fruchtlos and bleibt mir kein anderes Mittel übrig.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Freundschaft grüssend</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ergebenst der Ihrige</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hugo Finck</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Meine Auslagen dieser zweite Sendung an Mssrs Watson &amp; Scull, London betragen 17 shillings = $4.25.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich würde Ihnen für wenige Samen von <name key="Eucalyptus%20citriodora">Eucalyptus citriodora</name> &amp; E. amygdalina sehr dankbar sein.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">H F</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Córdova<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mexico.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> 8 January 1885</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Ferdinand von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Respected Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will have received my letter of 6 December 1884, in which I [informed] you of the consignment of a tin box with acorns that I sent to you via London per Messrs Watson &amp; Scull, Thames Street.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Per steamer <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Esk</seg> I sent under similar address a second consignment of acorns packed in a basket. The steamer left Vera Cruz for South Hampton on 2 January.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Enclosed leaf of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Fraxinus ? trilobata</seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <name key="Fraxinus%20trilobata">Fraxinus trilobata</name>
                        </seg>
                        <seg style=""> not in IPNI.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg> and a twig of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Quercus </seg>No 3 (Cozahual), also a leaf of a freshly germinated acorn of No 3.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 6. Quercus sp ? a deciduous oak, 60 to 80 feet high with excellent timber for all purposes. Its bark is used in tanning. Height above sea 7 to 9,000 feet.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 7. <name key="Quercus%20argentea">Quercus argentea</name>. Deciduous. 80 to 100 feet high; was formerly very abundant but now nearly extinquished. Good timber for building purposes &amp; durable. Is very ornamental. From 7 to 9,000 ft.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 8. Quercus sp ? deciduous, resembles No 7 in the colour of the leaves but is quite distinct; 60 to 80 ft high. Its timber is used by wheelwrights &amp; for building purposes. Is a very fine oak. 7 to 9,000 ft.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 9. Unknown oak, of which only a few acorns were delivered to me, without any leaves. 7 to 9,000 ft.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 0. Large leaved <name key="Quercus%20virens">Quercus virens</name>, live oak; 3,000 ft above sea. Could obtain only a few acorns, as most live oaks gave no fruit during last year.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This week I am sending a man into the mountains to collect pine and fir cones.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>All the various orders that I have given were fruitless and I have no other means left.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Friendly greetings</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Most humbly your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hugo Finck</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My expenses of this second consignment to Messrs Watson &amp; Scull, London, amount to 17 shillings = $4.25.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I would be very grateful to you for a few seeds of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Eucalyptus%20citriodora">Eucalyptus citriodora</name>
               </seg> and <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. amygdalina</seg>.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>H F</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus%20amygdalina">Eucalyptus amygdalina</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus%20citriodora">Eucalyptus citriodora</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Fraxinus%20trilobata">Fraxinus trilobata</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Quercus%20argentea">Quercus argentea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Quercus%20virens">Quercus virens</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
